<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>dig one’s heels in • dig oneself in</xh5><p> <i>dig one’s heels in—</i>act firmly; refuse to yield: It is not an indication of my lack of ability, but rather a sign that it is time for me to <u>dig my heels in</u> and exert more effort.</p><p> <i>dig oneself in</i>—(also: dig in) 1. <i>(of soldiers)</i> dig a protective place for oneself: We were ordered to <u>dig ourselves in</u> and I can assure you that it did not take us long to dig our trench. 2. establish oneself securely; get oneself settled (in a new job, etc.): I am relatively new to the photography world although I’ve <u>dug myself in</u> and tried to improve as much as I can.</p> </entry>
